{"id": "EUVD-2024-24242", "enisaUuid": "c603f02e-15fb-3a6c-87ab-0dadcd94ee6b", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nksmbd: fix slab-out-of-bounds in smb2_allocate_rsp_buf\n\nIf ->ProtocolId is SMB2_TRANSFORM_PROTO_NUM, smb2 request size\nvalidation could be skipped. if request size is smaller than\nsizeof(struct smb2_query_info_req), slab-out-of-bounds read can happen in\nsmb2_allocate_rsp_buf(). This patch allocate response buffer after\ndecrypting transform request. smb3_decrypt_req() will validate transform\nrequest size and avoid slab-out-of-bound in smb2_allocate_rsp_buf().", "datePublished": "2024-05-01T05:26:56", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-04T17:14:51", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/da21401372607c49972ea87a6edaafb36a17c325", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b80ba648714e6d790d69610cf14656be222d0248", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3160d9734453a40db248487f8204830879c207f1", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0977f89722eceba165700ea384f075143f012085", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c119f4ede3fa90a9463f50831761c28f989bfb20"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-26980"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "19c394d7-0f8a-3d75-83d8-acddfb754aeb", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "0626e6641f6b467447c81dd7678a69c66f7746cf <0977f89722eceba165700ea384f075143f012085"}, {"id": "2decd58d-51b3-37f1-8e86-8ac1b3d2a82b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.6.29"}, {"id": "5a01f56d-f0b1-3fc2-b3f1-016b9904c360", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.9"}, {"id": "6a32f490-bc6b-34ef-b184-f535ca5d2ce9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.88"}, {"id": "9709d671-6764-392e-8a41-71827e99caf8", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "0626e6641f6b467447c81dd7678a69c66f7746cf <da21401372607c49972ea87a6edaaf